      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic constitutive model with isotropic hardening; contact formulation captures screw-rod interface behavior; geometry derived from CAD.",
      "rationale": "The FEA employs a continuum elastoplastic model with bilinear isotropic hardening calibrated from coupon tensile tests of Ti-6Al-4V. Frictional contact (mu=0.2) at the screw-rod interface captures load transfer. Geometry faithfully reproduced from manufacturer CAD. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
