    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved Gradation 2 vs. required Gradation 3) is offset by the direct correspondence between the validation scenario and the COU, the multi-laboratory experimental dataset, and the conservative acceptance criteria applied. Overall credibility is sufficient to support a Medium assurance level decision for the non-cannulated pedicle screw FEA framework.",
